===Etymology===
Coined by Bell Labs supervisor Don Macpherson in the early 1960s [http://www.sigtel.com/tel_tech_octothorpe.html][http://www.word-detective.com/072999.html#octothorpe][http://www.quinion.com/words/weirdwords/ww-oct1.htm]; ''[[octo]]'' for the eight points, and ''[[thorpe]]'' after 1912 Olympic medalist [[wikipedia:Jim_Thorpe|Jim Thorpe]].

.

===Noun===
'''octothorpe'''

# The name for the # symbol. (''Rare - because very few people know this term.'')

